The Internet of Things (IoT) has enabled insurers to collect data from connected devices. Telematics devices in cars, for instance, transmit data on driving habits, location, and vehicle health, helping insurers determine appropriate premiums and offer discounts for safer driving.

Smart insurance leverages blockchain technology for faster and more secure claims processing. This reduces fraud and streamlines the claims approval process by creating a transparent, immutable ledger of transactions.

AI algorithms are used for risk assessment, fraud detection, and customer service in smart insurance. These systems can analyze vast amounts of data quickly, enabling insurers to make better-informed decisions.

Insurers employ chatbots and virtual assistants to enhance customer support. These AI-driven tools can answer policyholder queries, provide policy information, and even guide customers through the claims process, improving customer satisfaction.
